The paper deals with image segmentation using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of DeepLab 3, a specific method for image segmentation, suggests that the paper may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on dermoscopic images suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
